14/* ! \file */
15
16#ifndef ISC_HT_H
17#define ISC_HT_H 1
18
19#include <inttypes.h>
20#include <string.h>
21
22#include <isc/types.h>
23#include <isc/result.h>
24
25typedef struct isc_ht isc_ht_t;
26typedef struct isc_ht_iter isc_ht_iter_t;
27
28/*%
29 * Initialize hashtable at *htp, using memory context and size of (1<<bits)
30 *
31 * Requires:
32 *\li 'htp' is not NULL and '*htp' is NULL.
33 *\li 'mctx' is a valid memory context.
34 *\li 'bits' >=1 and 'bits' <=32
35 *
36 * Returns:
37 *\li #ISC_R_NOMEMORY -- not enough memory to create pool
38 *\li #ISC_R_SUCCESS -- all is well.
39 */
40isc_result_t
41isc_ht_init(isc_ht_t **htp, isc_mem_t *mctx, uint8_t bits);
42
43/*%
44 * Destroy hashtable, freeing everything
45 *
46 * Requires:
47 * \li '*htp' is valid hashtable
48 */
49void
50isc_ht_destroy(isc_ht_t **htp);
51
52/*%
53 * Add a node to hashtable, pointed by binary key 'key' of size 'keysize';
54 * set its value to 'value'
55 *
56 * Requires:
57 *\li 'ht' is a valid hashtable
58 *
59 * Returns:
60 *\li #ISC_R_NOMEMORY -- not enough memory to create pool
61 *\li #ISC_R_EXISTS -- node of the same key already exists
62 *\li #ISC_R_SUCCESS -- all is well.
63 */
64isc_result_t
65isc_ht_add(isc_ht_t *ht, const unsigned char *key, uint32_t keysize,
66 void *value);
67
68/*%
69 * Find a node matching 'key'/'keysize' in hashtable 'ht';
70 * if found, set '*valuep' to its value. (If 'valuep' is NULL,
71 * then simply return SUCCESS or NOTFOUND to indicate whether the
72 * key exists in the hashtable.)
73 *
74 * Requires:
75 * \li 'ht' is a valid hashtable
76 *
77 * Returns:
78 * \li #ISC_R_SUCCESS -- success
79 * \li #ISC_R_NOTFOUND -- key not found
80 */
81isc_result_t
82isc_ht_find(const isc_ht_t *ht, const unsigned char *key,
83 uint32_t keysize, void **valuep);
84
85/*%
86 * Delete node from hashtable
87 *
88 * Requires:
89 *\li ht is a valid hashtable
90 *
91 * Returns:
92 *\li #ISC_R_NOTFOUND -- key not found
93 *\li #ISC_R_SUCCESS -- all is well
94 */
95isc_result_t
96isc_ht_delete(isc_ht_t *ht, const unsigned char *key, uint32_t keysize);
97
98/*%
99 * Create an iterator for the hashtable; point '*itp' to it.
100 *
101 * Requires:
102 *\li 'ht' is a valid hashtable
103 *\li 'itp' is non NULL and '*itp' is NULL.
104 */
105isc_result_t
106isc_ht_iter_create(isc_ht_t *ht, isc_ht_iter_t **itp);
107
108/*%
109 * Destroy the iterator '*itp', set it to NULL
110 *
111 * Requires:
112 *\li 'itp' is non NULL and '*itp' is non NULL.
113 */
114void
115isc_ht_iter_destroy(isc_ht_iter_t **itp);
116
117/*%
118 * Set an iterator to the first entry.
119 *
120 * Requires:
121 *\li 'it' is non NULL.
122 *
123 * Returns:
124 * \li #ISC_R_SUCCESS -- success
125 * \li #ISC_R_NOMORE -- no data in the hashtable
126 */
127isc_result_t
128isc_ht_iter_first(isc_ht_iter_t *it);
129
130/*%
131 * Set an iterator to the next entry.
132 *
133 * Requires:
134 *\li 'it' is non NULL.
135 *
136 * Returns:
137 * \li #ISC_R_SUCCESS -- success
138 * \li #ISC_R_NOMORE -- end of hashtable reached
139 */
140isc_result_t
141isc_ht_iter_next(isc_ht_iter_t *it);
142
143/*%
144 * Delete current entry and set an iterator to the next entry.
145 *
146 * Requires:
147 *\li 'it' is non NULL.
148 *
149 * Returns:
150 * \li #ISC_R_SUCCESS -- success
151 * \li #ISC_R_NOMORE -- end of hashtable reached
152 */
153isc_result_t
154isc_ht_iter_delcurrent_next(isc_ht_iter_t *it);
155
156
157/*%
158 * Set 'value' to the current value under the iterator
159 *
160 * Requires:
161 *\li 'it' is non NULL.
162 *\li 'valuep' is non NULL and '*valuep' is NULL.
163 */
164void
165isc_ht_iter_current(isc_ht_iter_t *it, void **valuep);
166
167/*%
168 * Set 'key' and 'keysize to the current key and keysize for the value
169 * under the iterator
170 *
171 * Requires:
172 *\li 'it' is non NULL.
173 *\li 'key' is non NULL and '*key' is NULL.
174 *\li 'keysize' is non NULL.
175 */
176void
177isc_ht_iter_currentkey(isc_ht_iter_t *it, unsigned char **key, size_t *keysize);
178
179/*%
180 * Returns the number of items in the hashtable.
181 *
182 * Requires:
183 *\li 'ht' is a valid hashtable
184 */
185unsigned int
186isc_ht_count(isc_ht_t *ht);
187#endif
188
